24/08/2005
RIMINI, Italy -- Minister of Environment Altero Matteoli and Macedonian counterpart Zoran Sapuric sealed a bilateral accord on co-operation Tuesday (23 August) during Sapuric's visit to Italy. The two discussed ways to enhance collaboration in environmental protection as well as Macedonia's application for official EU candidate status. 
In other news, Macedonian Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva pays a daylong working visit to Denmark on Wednesday. Skopje's Euro-Atlantic integration bid is expected to dominate the agenda. (Macedonian Government Web site, Makfax - 24/08/05; Macedonian Radio - 23/08/05)
